{
  "texts": [
    "RT-PCR amplification of cir-cRNAs requires two sets of RT-PCR primers (Dudekula et al. 2016; Zhong et al. 2018 Zhong et al., 2019;; Nielsen et al. 2022).",
    "Divergent RT-PCR primers are used to amplify the claimed circRNA by facing towards and amplifying across the circRNA BSJ (Dudekula et al. 2016; Zhong et al. 2018 Zhong et al., 2019;; Nielsen et al. 2022).",
    "Divergent RT-PCR primers should therefore not amplify linear transcripts from the host or any other human gene.",
    "In contrast, convergent RT-PCR primers are employed to amplify linear transcripts, typically from the claimed host gene (Dudekula et al. 2016; Zhong et al. 2018 Zhong et al., 2019;; Nielsen et al. 2022).",
    "For claimed divergent RT-PCR primers, forward and reverse primers were first queried on circPRIMER (Zhong et al. 2018) using standard settings (Fig. 2)."
  ]
}